One striking aspect of Israel-Gaza conflict is how Darwinian it is. Dead IDF soldier families hiring companies to have the sperm harvested from their cadavers for use in IVF, Palestinian families trading children between households to ensure a male heir survives a deadly bombing.

Both sides seem preoccupied with "passing genes", making sure the dead soldiers get to have an offspring survive them, etc. and have developed strategies as to achieve it. I have also posted my prediction before that Israel will be the first state to start using artificial wombs.

I've said it before, but I can never dislike pit bulls much now, because I remember how sadly my seaside cousin's pit bull was crying all night on the last day of summer before the winter when his grandma died. That dog really loved the old woman and mourned her while still alive

I remember waking up at 4 AM with the most sorrowful whining of all time coming from under the window where the pit bull slept, September sea roaring in the distance. Must be very helpless to be a dog and sense someone you love will pass away soon, but you can't do much about it.
